        "created_at": "2022-07-06T12:31:18Z",
        "updated_at": "2022-07-06T12:31:18Z",
        "author_association": "NONE",
        "body": "I can understand that but, I think it would be great for many people if these features would be considered.\r\n\r\nBrowsers and the [WebSockets Living Standard](https://websockets.spec.whatwg.org/) do indeed not offer pings and pongs. They also don't offer an option to set a pingInterval or any internal ping support and yet OkHttp _does_.\r\n\r\nAlso the standard mentions that pings and pongs are not exposed in the api but does not give a reason why. Actually the standard does the opposite. It mentions [reasons](https://websockets.spec.whatwg.org/#ping-and-pong-frames) why it would be good to expose this functionality (even though it does not).",
